<p><strong>Back in January, Oklahoma Senator Ralph Shortey proposed legislation to ban the production of aborted fetal cell-derived flavor chemicals in his home state</strong>. If passed, S.B. 1418 would also reportedly ban the sale of any products that contain flavor chemicals derived from human fetal tissue, which includes Pepsi products as well as products produced by Kraft and Nestle (<a href="http://www.naturalnews.com/034777_Pepsi_aborted_fetus_cells_soda_flavoring.html" target="_blank">http://www.naturalnews.com</a>)<br />
